Definition.WordDefinition: Atlanta \At*lan"ta\, n. [NL., fr. Gr. ?.] (Zo["o]l.) A genus of small glassy heteropod mollusks found swimming at the surface in mid ocean. See {Heteropod}. [1913 Webster]

Atlanta n 1: state capital and largest city of Georgia; chief commercial center of the southeastern United States; was plundered and burned by Sherman's army during the American Civil War [syn: {capital of Georgia}] 2: Federal troops under Sherman cut off the railroads supplying Atlanta and burned the city; 1864 [syn: {battle of Atlanta}]
